{"lemma":"شِدَّةُ","slug":"شِدَّةُ","root":"ش.د.د","root_slug":"ش-د-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-د-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n21914","n21915","n21954","n21955","n21956","n21957"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%90%D8%AF%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of شَدَّ (šadda)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"intensity","tags":["uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"strength, severity, violence","tags":["uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"misfortune, misery, distress, hardship, discomfort, affliction","tags":["countable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"shadda"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Verbal noun of شَدَّ (šadda).\n\nInstance noun of شَدَّ (šadda, “to geminate”)."},"ipa":["/ʃid.da/","/ʃad.da/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n21914","headword_ar":"شَدَّةٌ","root":"$d","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[inf. n. of un. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ad~ahu","text_ar":"شَدَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": as such signifying]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A single act"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of making,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rendering, hard, firm, compact,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sound; strong, powerful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forcible:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of binding,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tying, firmly, fast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strongly."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b2-  See also 2, last sentence but one.       -A2-  Also [inf. n. of un. of the intrans. verb"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ad~a","text_ar":"شَدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": as such signifying]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A single charge"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assault"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"attack"},{"kind":"text","text":"in war or battle. (S, A, * Mgh, L, K. *)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n21915","headword_ar":"شِدَّةٌ","root":"$d","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ad~a","text_ar":"شَدَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, Msb) as syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ai$otad~a","text_ar":"اِشْتَدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L:) [and] a subst. from [i. e. syn. with]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ai$otidaAdN","text_ar":"اِشْتِدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"attribute denoted by the epithet"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$adiydN","text_ar":"شَدِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hardness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, MA, L,) in substances and in attributes; (L;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"firmness, compactness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soundness; strength, power,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"force; vigour, robustness, sturdiness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hardiness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA, L; see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ud~N","text_ar":"اَشُدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which, accord. to some, is a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$id~apN","text_ar":"شِدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"courage, bravery, firmness of heart:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"niggardliness, tenaciousness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"avarice:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A: [see also 5, last sentence:])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehemence, violence, intenseness, stress, pressure, severity, strictness, rigour, tightness, straitness"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"difficulty:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hardship, rigour of fortune:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA, L:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"famine, dearth, want of victuals; hardness, straitness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"difficulty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of subsistence [&c.]: (L:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trouble, distress, affliction, calamity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adversity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA, L;) as also [↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ud~aY","text_ar":"شُدَّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", in these as well as in some of the preceding senses, and] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$adiydapN","text_ar":"شَدِيدَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [rather meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a hard,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distressing, event, an affliction,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a calamity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and rarely used,] of which, (L,) or of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$id~apN","text_ar":"شِدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (MA, L,) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$adaAy^idu","text_ar":"شَدَايِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (MA, L,) agreeably with analogy if of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$adiydapN","text_ar":"شَدِيدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but extr. if of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$id~apN","text_ar":"شِدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and this pl. also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seditions, discords,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dissensions, whereby men are put into a state of commotion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rigours,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pangs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gamaraAt","text_ar":"غَمَرَات"},{"kind":"text","text":",) of death: (S and Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gmr","text_ar":"غمر"},{"kind":"text","text":":) accord. to Sb, the pl of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$id~apN","text_ar":"شِدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$idadN","text_ar":"شِدَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which, he says, preserves its original form [without idghám] because it does not resemble a verb. (L.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAsayotu minohu $id~apF","text_ar":"قَاسَيْتُ مِنْهُ شِدَّةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I endured, from him, hardness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from it, hardship,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnK","text_ar":"فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xfotu $ud~aY","text_ar":"خفْتُ شُدَّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$id~atahu","text_ar":"شِدَّتَهُ"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1519},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I feared the hardness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of such a one"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: so says AZ: and he cites this verse:"},{"kind":"quote","text":"↓ \n      faA_in~iY laA A^aliynu liqawoli $ud~aY\n                      \n                     \n                        mina AlHadiydi ↓ \n      walawo kaAnato A^a$ad~a"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for, I will not become gentle for a hard saying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a saying of hardness,"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"though it should be harder than iron"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSaAbatoniY","text_ar":"اَصَابَتْنِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ud~aY","text_ar":"شُدَّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$id~apN","text_ar":"شِدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hardship,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"befell me"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (AZ, S.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$id~apN","text_ar":"شِدَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A strong, an intense,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a great, degree"},{"kind":"text","text":"of any quality &c.]"}],"source_refs":["L","Msb","K","S","A","MA"]},{"entry_id":"n21954","headword_ar":"شُدِهَ","root":"$dh","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (JK, S, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$adohN","text_ar":"شَدْهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, JK, S)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became confounded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perplexed, and unable to see his right course;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became bereft of his reason"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intellect; i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duhi$a","text_ar":"دُهِشَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (JK, S, K:) and also, (K,) or, accord. to AZ, only, (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, busied, occupied,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"employed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"busied,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so as to be diverted"},{"kind":"text","text":"from something; or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"diverted"},{"kind":"text","text":"from a thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by being busied;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ugila","text_ar":"شُغِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was caused to become confounded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perplexed, and unable to see his right course;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"An$dh","text_ar":"انشده","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A$tdh","text_ar":"اشتده","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, accord. to different copies: the former accord. to the TA.) Accord. to Az,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$adohN","text_ar":"شَدْهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~aha$u","text_ar":"الدَّهَشُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as it is thought to be by some [and as is implied by what here follows]. (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$adahahu","text_ar":"شَدَهَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He confounded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perplexed, him, so that he was unable to see his right course;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bereft him of his reason"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intellect;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adoha$ahu","text_ar":"اَدْهَشَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A$dhhu","text_ar":"اشدههُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A 'Obeyd, K:) or the former verb, in the act. form, has not been heard: (Har p. 64:) and [it is asserted that] one does not say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A$dhhu","text_ar":"اشدههُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (JK.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$adaha raA^osahu","text_ar":"شَدَهَ رَاْسَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$adaxahu","text_ar":"شَدَخَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He broke his head"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.)"}],"source_refs":["JK","S","K"]},{"entry_id":"n21955","headword_ar":"شَدْهٌ","root":"$dh","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see what next follows."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n21956","headword_ar":"شُدْهٌ","root":"$dh","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$adahN","text_ar":"شَدَهٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, and so in some copies of the K and in the TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$adohN","text_ar":"شَدْهٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(so in some copies of the K in the place of the second, and in others together with the second, and in the TA) [app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A state of confusion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perplexity, so that one is unable to see his right course;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a state of alienation of mind;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] substs. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$udiha","text_ar":"شُدِهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S: [but in the K they are mentioned after"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$adahahu","text_ar":"شَدَهَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$odahahu","text_ar":"اَشْدَهَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adoha$ahu","text_ar":"اَدْهَشَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$aAdihu","text_ar":"مَشَادِهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$aAgilu","text_ar":"مَشَاغِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as being the substs.; so that they may signify as above, and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"business, occupation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"employment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; agreeably with renderings in the TK:]) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$udaAhN","text_ar":"شُدَاهٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$udiha","text_ar":"شُدِهَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. in the former, or in both, of these senses]. (K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K"]},{"entry_id":"n21957","headword_ar":"شَدَهٌ","root":"$dh","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next preceding paragraph."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}